CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, May 2, 1959, pg. 12, reads: "Love's Labor's Lost...Sometimes Home is Where the Heart Remains - Bought for $2800 - The above spacious house at 2215 Webster Ave. was owned by Sanford and Mattie Mitchell. It has a large yard in rear leading to a paved alley.  It was sold to the Dwelling Building and Loan Association in 1943 for $2800."
TitMainTitle: Three story faux brick house with mansard roof, two chimneys on left, and broken windows, 2215 Webster Avenue, Hill District
